# TypeScript conventions

## Type discipline

- strict: true always
- Never `any` â€” use `unknown` and narrow
- Discriminated unions over optional fields for state
- Type-only imports: `import type { Foo }`
- Result types over throw for handleable failures

## Patterns

- `as const` over `enum`
- `satisfies` over type assertion
- `readonly` for immutable arrays + props
- Brand types for IDs when mixing is risky

## Async

- async/await over .then chains
- Handle rejections explicitly
- Promise.all parallel, allSettled for partial success

## Banned

- `any`
- `// @ts-ignore` (use `// @ts-expect-error`)
- Unsafe `x as Foo` where `satisfies` works
- Mutating function parameters
- `enum` (use union literals + `as const`)
- `} catch {}`

## Tsconfig extras beyond strict

- noUncheckedIndexedAccess
- noImplicitOverride
- exactOptionalPropertyTypes
- noFallthroughCasesInSwitch
